<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 1:10PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Meagher
County through 200 PM MDT...
At 109 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles southeast of White Sulphur Springs, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lennep and Ringling.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
